For An Act To Be Entitled
8
9 AN ACT TO PROVIDE A SAFETY VALVE FOR A MINOR
10 DEFENDANT WHO IS ALSO A VICTIM OF HUMAN TRAFFICKING;
11 TO AMEND THE HUMAN TRAFFICKING ACT OF 2013; TO CREATE
12 AN APPEAL RIGHT FOR A MINOR DEFENDANT WHO IS ALSO A
13 VICTIM OF HUMAN TRAFFICKING; AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES.
14
15
Subtitle
16
17 TO PROVIDE A SAFETY VALVE AND APPEAL
18 RIGHT FOR A MINOR DEFENDANT WHO IS ALSO
19 A VICTIM OF HUMAN TRAFFICKING; AND TO
20 AMEND THE HUMAN TRAFFICKING ACT OF 2013.
21
22 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
23
24 SECTION 1. DO NOT CODIFY. Legislative intent.
25 The General Assembly intends for courts to consider whether a minor has
26 been a victim of human trafficking before transferring a delinquency matter
27 to the criminal division of circuit court or imposing a sentence upon the
28 person.
29
30 SECTION 2. Arkansas Code § 5-2-210 is amended to read as follows:
31 5-2-210. Human trafficking — Affirmative defense.
32 (a) As used in this section,:
33 (1) "Nonviolent criminal offense" means a criminal offense that
34 does not constitute a violent crime as defined in § 16-90-1101; and
35 (2) “victim Victim of trafficking of persons” means a person who
36 has been subjected to trafficking of persons, § 5-18-103.
