1 (b) It If a person is eighteen (18) years of age or older, it is an
2 affirmative defense to prosecution for an offense listed under subsection (c)
3 of this section if at the time a person engaged in the conduct charged to
4 constitute the offense the person was:
5 (1) A victim of trafficking of persons; and
6 (2) Engaged in the offense as a direct result of the trafficking
7 of persons.
8 (c) The affirmative defense under this section may be raised only in a
9 prosecution for one (1) or more of the following offenses:
10 (1) Forgery, § 5-37-201;
11 (2) Defrauding a prospective adoptive parent, § 5-37-216;
12 (3) A prostitution offense under § 5-70-101 et seq.;
13 (4) Obscene performance at a live public show, § 5-68-305; or
14 (5) A controlled substance offense under § 5-64-401 et seq. § 5-
15 64-402 et seq. that is not a Class Y felony.
16 (d) If a person is seventeen (17) years of age or younger, it is an
17 affirmative defense to prosecution for a nonviolent criminal offense if at
18 the time a person engaged in the conduct charged to constitute the offense
19 the person was:
20 (1) A victim of trafficking of persons; and
21 (2) Engaged in the offense as a direct result of the trafficking
22 of persons.
23
24 SECTION 3. Arkansas Code § 5-18-103(a) and (b), concerning the offense
25 of trafficking of persons, are amended to read as follows:
26 (a) A person commits the offense of trafficking of persons if he or
27 she knowingly:
28 (1) Recruits, harbors, transports, obtains, entices, solicits,
29 isolates, provides, or maintains a person when he or she knows or reasonably
30 should know that the person will be subjected to involuntary servitude;
31 (2) Benefits financially or benefits by receiving anything of
32 value from participation in a venture that he or she knows or reasonably
33 should know is engaged in conduct prohibited under subdivision (a)(1) of this
34 section;
35 (3) Subjects a person to involuntary servitude;
36 (4) Recruits, entices, solicits, isolates, harbors, transports,
2 04-14-2025 14:29:29 CEB232

As Engrossed: H4/14/25 SB620
1 provides, maintains, or obtains a minor for commercial sexual activity;
2 (5) Sells or offers to sell travel services that he or she knows
3 or reasonably should know include an activity prohibited under subdivisions
4 (a)(1)-(4) of this section;
5 (6) Recruits, entices, solicits, isolates, harbors, transports,
6 provides, maintains, or obtains a pregnant woman for the purpose of causing
7 the pregnant woman to place her unborn child for adoption by:
8 (A) The use of or threatened use of physical force;
9 (B) The physical restraint or threat of physical restraint
10 of a person;
11 (C) Serious physical injury or threat of serious physical
12 injury to a person;
13 (D) Abuse or threatened abuse of law or legal process;
14 (E) Any scheme, plan, or pattern that has a purpose to
15 cause the pregnant woman to believe that, if the pregnant woman does not
16 place the unborn child for adoption, a person would suffer serious physical
17 injury or physical restraint; or
18 (F) Means of serious harm or threats of serious harm to a
19 person; or
20 (7) Benefits financially or benefits by receiving anything of
21 value from participating in an act described under subdivision (a)(6) of this
22 section; or
23 (8) Recruits, entices, solicits, isolates, harbors, transports,
24 provides, maintains, or obtains a minor for the purpose of causing the minor
25 to join or remain in a criminal organization or engage in a violation of
26 criminal law by:
27 (A) The use or threatened use of physical force;
28 (B) The causing of serious physical harm to another
29 person;
30 (C) The threat of causing serious physical harm to another
31 person;
32 (D) Coercion, duress, or menace; or
33 (E) Any scheme, plan, or pattern that has a purpose to
34 cause a minor to believe that, if the minor does not join or remain in the
35 criminal organization or engage in a violation of criminal law, another
36 person would suffer serious harm.
